1
00:00:01,502 --> 00:00:02,503
[Mouse squeaks]

2
00:00:02,503 --> 00:00:04,046
[Penguins chirp]

3
00:00:05,130 --> 00:00:06,089
[Screeches]

4
00:00:06,131 --> 00:00:08,258
[All cheering]

5
00:00:10,302 --> 00:00:11,303
[Screeches]

6
00:00:11,303 --> 00:00:12,804
[Quacks]

7
00:00:13,555 --> 00:00:14,640
J "Adventure Time" J

8
00:00:14,681 --> 00:00:16,058
s Come on, grab your friends 7

9
00:00:16,141 --> 00:00:18,727
J We're going to
very distant lands J

10
00:00:18,769 --> 00:00:21,021
J With Jake the dog
and Finn the human &

11
00:00:21,146 --> 00:00:22,648
J The fun will never end J

12
00:00:22,648 --> 00:00:24,483
J It's "Adventure Time"“ J

13
00:00:35,713 --> 00:00:36,839
[Gasps]

14
00:00:36,839 --> 00:00:38,549
Whew.

15
00:00:38,591 --> 00:00:41,427
A goblet of sparkling
apple juice for milady.

16
00:00:41,552 --> 00:00:42,470
Thanks, Finn.

17
00:00:43,805 --> 00:00:46,599
Hey...where'd you get
this goblet?

18
00:00:46,683 --> 00:00:49,310
Oh, uh, I think we won it
in a fight with an octopus

19
00:00:49,352 --> 00:00:52,480
we were fighting in, like,
a sea cave full of treasure?

20
00:00:52,563 --> 00:00:53,356
(\\[o

21
00:00:53,356 --> 00:00:56,234
It was from when BMO was
playing dress-up.

22
00:00:56,359 --> 00:01:00,363
It reminds me
of a cup my uncle used to have.

23
00:01:00,446 --> 00:01:02,115
You mean your Uncle Gumbald,
right?

24
00:01:02,198 --> 00:01:03,616
Do tell.

25
00:01:03,616 --> 00:01:05,326
You never talk
about your family.

26
00:01:05,451 --> 00:01:06,911
I don't know.

27
00:01:06,953 --> 00:01:08,538
Families are tricky.

28
00:01:08,579 --> 00:01:10,164
You guys know what I mean,
right?

29
00:01:13,334 --> 00:01:17,964
We have to go back a ways,
like 800 years ago.

30
00:01:48,870 --> 00:01:50,496
[Whirs, beeps]

31
00:02:04,218 --> 00:02:05,219
[Glass shatters]

32
00:02:19,942 --> 00:02:21,194
[Sighs]

33
00:02:21,277 --> 00:02:22,904
GOBLIN: Help!

34
00:02:22,945 --> 00:02:24,781
Help me!

35
00:02:25,323 --> 00:02:27,450
Oh, goodness me.

36
00:02:29,035 --> 00:02:31,579
Someone please help me.

37
00:02:31,662 --> 00:02:35,291
I'm a defenseless little goblin
surrounded by all this loot.

38
00:02:35,333 --> 00:02:36,834
Boo-hoe.

39
00:02:36,918 --> 00:02:38,211
[Animal grunts]

40
00:02:39,295 --> 00:02:41,839
Oh, you poor thing.
Here.

41
00:02:41,923 --> 00:02:44,217
Have a drink to ease your nerves
while I untie you.

42
00:02:44,342 --> 00:02:45,676
Pfft!

43
00:02:45,718 --> 00:02:46,969
Aah!

44
00:02:47,053 --> 00:02:49,430
The time for faking is over now.

45
00:02:49,472 --> 00:02:51,557
Give me all your stuff.

46
00:02:51,599 --> 00:02:53,226
[Chuckles] What?

47
00:02:53,351 --> 00:02:56,187
You brought a peashooter
to a techno-harpoon fight?!

48
00:02:56,229 --> 00:02:57,605
-[Snap]
- Aah!

49
00:02:57,688 --> 00:02:58,564
[Groans]

50
00:02:58,606 --> 00:03:00,358
Aah-aah-aaah!

51
00:03:04,362 --> 00:03:07,990
[Slurping]

52
00:03:08,074 --> 00:03:09,367
Mm?

53
00:03:10,993 --> 00:03:13,204
Another close call today, Neddy.

54
00:03:15,122 --> 00:03:16,833
[Squeals]

55
00:03:16,874 --> 00:03:18,000
[Whimpers]

56
00:03:19,210 --> 00:03:21,504
Neddy, you sweet chicken.

57
00:03:21,629 --> 00:03:24,382
[Beatboxing]

58
00:03:30,763 --> 00:03:33,015
It was a lot different
back in the Mother Gum.

59
00:03:33,099 --> 00:03:35,977
-[Squeaks]
- We all had each other's backs.

60
00:03:37,228 --> 00:03:39,397
I'm going to make more of us,
Neddy.

61
00:03:40,273 --> 00:03:42,483
I know you don't care,
and that's fine.

62
00:03:42,525 --> 00:03:46,028
But I need to be
around people like me.

63
00:03:53,369 --> 00:03:55,288
O-kay!

64
00:03:55,371 --> 00:03:57,498
This is it, Neddy.

65
00:03:57,540 --> 00:03:59,667
We're getting relatives!

66
00:04:01,502 --> 00:04:03,045
[Electricity crackles]

67
00:04:04,422 --> 00:04:06,924
[Whimpers]

68
00:04:07,049 --> 00:04:08,676
[Grunts]

69
00:04:10,678 --> 00:04:12,179
[Sizzling]

70
00:04:12,179 --> 00:04:14,807
[Laughs] It worked!

71
00:04:14,891 --> 00:04:16,684
Your name's Aunt Lolly!

72
00:04:16,767 --> 00:04:19,145
A pleasure to meet you, dear.

73
00:04:19,228 --> 00:04:23,399
And you're Cousin Chicle.
You're a full 2.3 meters tall.

74
00:04:23,482 --> 00:04:26,152
Naturally. I am a gentleman
of high standing.

75
00:04:26,235 --> 00:04:27,778
Oh, Cousin Chicle.

76
00:04:27,904 --> 00:04:32,033
And finally, Uncle Gumbald!

77
00:04:32,158 --> 00:04:34,285
This is your favorite mug.

78
00:04:34,368 --> 00:04:35,536
Ah, yes.

79
00:04:35,536 --> 00:04:37,371
I'm your great uncle.

80
00:04:37,413 --> 00:04:39,373
The mug proclaims it so.

81
00:04:39,415 --> 00:04:41,417
Aren't they great, Neddy?

82
00:04:41,500 --> 00:04:46,047
You'll be my protectors,
my advisers, my family.

83
00:04:46,047 --> 00:04:47,548
[Whimpers]

84
00:05:07,318 --> 00:05:08,945
Hmm.

85
00:05:17,203 --> 00:05:19,580
I'm heading out, Neddy.
What?

86
00:05:20,206 --> 00:05:21,582
What?

87
00:05:21,582 --> 00:05:23,960
What?!

88
00:05:24,043 --> 00:05:25,836
Morning, small niece.

89
00:05:25,836 --> 00:05:28,547
Uncle Gumbald,
the taffy trees are gone!

90
00:05:28,589 --> 00:05:31,342
I know.
I chopped 'em down last night.

91
00:05:32,093 --> 00:05:34,345
Yesterday,
I realized these trees

92
00:05:34,428 --> 00:05:37,306
were not being utilized
to their full potential,

93
00:05:37,348 --> 00:05:40,101
so I elected to build
this cabin.

94
00:05:40,226 --> 00:05:41,936
This is but the first step

95
00:05:41,978 --> 00:05:44,480
in building my glorious
new candy city.

96
00:05:45,731 --> 00:05:47,733
I've already drawn up
the plans for it.

97
00:05:47,858 --> 00:05:50,486
All of this will be apartments.

98
00:05:50,569 --> 00:05:53,698
And did you notice
the family crest I designed?

99
00:05:53,739 --> 00:05:56,867
It's a "G" for, uh..."Gum."

100
00:05:57,994 --> 00:05:59,870
Why does it look like your head?

101
00:05:59,954 --> 00:06:02,999
[Laughs] You're such a curious
little girl.

102
00:06:03,124 --> 00:06:06,002
We're a lifestyle brand now.

103
00:06:19,265 --> 00:06:20,141
[Grunts]

104
00:06:27,023 --> 00:06:28,649
Success!

105
00:06:28,733 --> 00:06:31,152
Now instead of worrying
about his dumb city,

106
00:06:31,235 --> 00:06:33,279
Uncle can come here
to picnic, swim,

107
00:06:33,279 --> 00:06:36,032
and, uh...fish!

108
00:06:39,160 --> 00:06:40,911
[Electricity crackles]

109
00:06:40,995 --> 00:06:43,164
Welcome to life, Candyfish.

110
00:06:43,164 --> 00:06:46,000
[Gasps]
I can't breathe air!

111
00:06:46,042 --> 00:06:47,543
UNCLE GUMBALD: Bonnie!

112
00:06:47,626 --> 00:06:50,046
What have you done
to my building site?

113
00:06:50,129 --> 00:06:53,424
I made us a butterscotch lake
and a fish to live in it.

114
00:06:53,549 --> 00:06:55,801
But that's where
the gift shop was gonna go.

115
00:06:55,885 --> 00:06:58,429
Now it's just gonna be
volleyballs, water skis,

116
00:06:58,512 --> 00:07:00,139
and shrimp cocktails.

117
00:07:00,181 --> 00:07:01,682
Sounds nice.

118
00:07:02,433 --> 00:07:05,311
Did you say you "made"
this creature?

119
00:07:05,394 --> 00:07:06,562
Come on.

120
00:07:06,645 --> 00:07:09,065
You'll appreciate him more
once you watch him swim around.

121
00:07:11,567 --> 00:07:16,697
Bonnibel...you've micromanaged
me for the last time.

122
00:07:19,325 --> 00:07:20,785
Huh?

123
00:07:22,953 --> 00:07:24,205
Hmm.

124
00:07:24,288 --> 00:07:28,709
I think it's time for Bonnie
to be re-branded.

125
00:07:30,419 --> 00:07:33,547
Niece, now that I've had
to stare at it for weeks,

126
00:07:33,589 --> 00:07:37,343
I've got to admit that
your lake was a very good idea.

127
00:07:37,468 --> 00:07:40,471
- Ja! Sehr gut!
- Very wunderbar.

128
00:07:40,596 --> 00:07:42,223
Oh, I'm so happy.

129
00:07:42,306 --> 00:07:44,975
We got you a gift to say thanks.

130
00:07:45,059 --> 00:07:46,977
It's right outside, Prinzessin.

131
00:07:48,354 --> 00:07:50,856
[Gasps]
You got me a car?

132
00:07:50,981 --> 00:07:52,441
Yes, a car.

133
00:07:52,483 --> 00:07:55,236
But also...a boyfriend!

134
00:07:55,236 --> 00:07:57,738
Hi, babe. Beep beep!

135
00:07:57,738 --> 00:07:59,615
Wait, what?

136
00:07:59,698 --> 00:08:02,993
All right, you nut.
Have fun on your date.

137
00:08:02,993 --> 00:08:04,078
Date?!

138
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:05,121
-[Engine starts]
- Let's go, babe.

139
00:08:05,204 --> 00:08:06,372
Beep beep!

140
00:08:06,455 --> 00:08:07,957
[Tires screech]

141
00:08:09,875 --> 00:08:12,628
What a naive little child.

142
00:08:16,090 --> 00:08:17,591
Date's over, babe.

143
00:08:17,633 --> 00:08:20,761
Pick you up tomorrow
to get matching tattoos.

144
00:08:22,763 --> 00:08:24,974
I'm back
from that terrible date.

145
00:08:25,015 --> 00:08:26,100
Hello?

146
00:08:26,142 --> 00:08:27,268
UNCLE GUMBALD:
Thank you for coming

147
00:08:27,268 --> 00:08:29,103
to the mandatory
optimization meeting.

148
00:08:29,145 --> 00:08:31,021
Tonight, we address...

149
00:08:31,021 --> 00:08:32,481
the "Bonnie problem."

150
00:08:32,523 --> 00:08:34,191
Bonnie problem?

151
00:08:34,316 --> 00:08:37,695
Our future city is on course
to be a rousing success,

152
00:08:37,695 --> 00:08:39,196
barring only one obstacle --

153
00:08:39,280 --> 00:08:42,074
our complete lack
of competent leadership.

154
00:08:42,158 --> 00:08:44,952
BB's the leader?
I thought she was a mime.

155
00:08:44,952 --> 00:08:47,329
'Cause I never hear
a word she says.

156
00:08:47,413 --> 00:08:49,331
- Oh, Cousin Chicle!
- Oh, Cousin Chicle!

157
00:08:49,415 --> 00:08:51,834
Dang, Chicle, that's cold.

158
00:08:51,917 --> 00:08:54,920
I have formulated a happy juice
that will render her

159
00:08:54,962 --> 00:08:57,840
as docile and simple-minded
as her cutie BF,

160
00:08:57,840 --> 00:08:59,592
young Mr. Creampuff.

161
00:08:59,675 --> 00:09:00,968
[Gasps]

162
00:09:01,051 --> 00:09:04,471
All we have to do is sprinkle
some of this on her breakfast,

163
00:09:04,471 --> 00:09:06,932
and we'll be in charge.

164
00:09:08,851 --> 00:09:12,688
Let us celebrate
with coup d'etat cupcakes.

165
00:09:14,982 --> 00:09:16,317
Poisoned cakes.

166
00:09:16,358 --> 00:09:18,110
[Poof!]

167
00:09:18,235 --> 00:09:20,321
Where am I?

168
00:09:22,698 --> 00:09:24,450
Oh, right, the poison.

169
00:09:24,491 --> 00:09:25,618
[Poof!]

170
00:09:25,743 --> 00:09:28,370
I don't know what's happening!

171
00:09:28,454 --> 00:09:30,080
VL EERIEE
- Whee! Whee!

172
00:09:30,122 --> 00:09:33,250
Ah! My first candy employees.

173
00:09:33,751 --> 00:09:35,336
What have you done?

174
00:09:35,377 --> 00:09:37,504
This isn't
what I made you to be.

175
00:09:37,630 --> 00:09:40,758
No, you wanted us to be
lowly pet fish,

176
00:09:40,841 --> 00:09:43,510
swimming
in your narcissistic pond.

177
00:09:43,510 --> 00:09:45,721
But I am your equal!

178
00:09:45,763 --> 00:09:48,641
You're not like me.
You're bad.

179
00:09:48,724 --> 00:09:50,893
I am the future.

180
00:09:50,893 --> 00:09:54,480
Come on, Bonnie.
Don't run away from happiness.

181
00:09:54,521 --> 00:09:56,357
I'm going to fix you.

182
00:09:56,398 --> 00:10:00,361
And then I'm going to fix
that sniveling gumwad, Neddy.

183
00:10:00,402 --> 00:10:02,404
Don't touch my brother!

184
00:10:02,488 --> 00:10:03,864
A pea-shooter?

185
00:10:08,160 --> 00:10:09,536
The juice!

186
00:10:09,620 --> 00:10:12,498
Nooooo!

187
00:10:14,291 --> 00:10:17,795
[Laughs] Hey!
Where's the party?

188
00:10:17,878 --> 00:10:19,171
[Goofy laughter]

189
00:10:19,296 --> 00:10:21,382
[Sighs] What a mess.

190
00:10:21,423 --> 00:10:26,303
But they do seem happier now,
so unburdened and pliable.

191
00:10:27,680 --> 00:10:30,683
You, the crunchy ball,
dance for me.

192
00:10:30,766 --> 00:10:32,142
Sure.

193
00:10:34,436 --> 00:10:37,064
Come on, lady.
Do the crunchy dance.

194
00:10:37,147 --> 00:10:38,399
Oh, Crunchy.

195
00:10:38,440 --> 00:10:40,776
Sure, I'll dance
with my candy people.

196
00:10:40,818 --> 00:10:43,445
Yay for the lady!

197
00:10:43,529 --> 00:10:45,906
BONNIBEL:
Call me...Princess.

198
00:10:45,948 --> 00:10:47,283
ALL: Hurrah!

199
00:10:49,702 --> 00:10:51,203
Whoa, for real?

200
00:10:51,287 --> 00:10:53,330
Like I said,
families are tricky.

201
00:10:54,707 --> 00:10:55,457
[Gasps]

202
00:10:56,834 --> 00:10:59,586
BMO!
Where did you get this cup?

203
00:10:59,670 --> 00:11:02,423
From that guy!
The guy on the cup!

204
00:11:02,548 --> 00:11:05,592
The guy whose face
is on the cup, that guy!

205
00:11:08,034 --> 00:11:11,871
s Come along with me J

206
00:11:11,913 --> 00:11:16,376
J And the butterflies and bees &

207
00:11:19,170 --> 00:11:21,547
This party is so crazy!

